dct_title_s: Outline map showing the triangulations made by the U.S. Coast Survey including the primary stations selected in 1875
dct_description_sm: Shows boundary between New York and New Jersey. At head of title: Geological Survey of New Jersey. "Lines of the United States Coast Survey triangulations are drawn in full black. Those selected in 1875 are drawn in broken lines." From: Annual report of the State Geologist, for the year 1875. Trenton, N.J. : [The Survey], 1875. Call no.: 8565.672.
dct_publisher_sm: [Trenton, N.J.] : Geological Survey of New Jersey, [1875] ([New York] : Julius Bien, Lith.)
